field.finalPrompt.description: Final drawing prompt for generating the image

field.elements.description: Drawing style for generating the image

field.traceId.description: Trace ID for tracking the request to generate the image, do not translate, keep as 'Trace ID'

description.aspect.message: --aspect, change the aspect ratio of the generated image, default value depends on the model and mode
description.aspect.description: Description of the aspect ratio parameter

description.chaos.message: --chaos, adjust the degree of variation in the generated image, the higher the number, the more unique and unexpected the generated image, range is 0-100, default is 1

description.fast.message: Ignore current settings, run a single generation task in 'fast mode', no default value

description.iw.message: --iw, set the importance of the image prompt relative to the text prompt during the generation process, range is 0-2, default is 1

description.no.message: --no, instruct the generation system to attempt to exclude certain elements, for example, '--no plants' will try to generate an image without plants, no default value

description.quality.message: --quality, set the quality and rendering time of the generated image, range is .25, .5, or 1, default is 1

description.random.message: Add random basic style codes to the prompts, use '--style random-16', '--style random-64', or '--style random-128' for different lengths of random style effects, no default value

description.relax.message: Override current settings, run a single task in 'slow mode', no default value

description.repeat.message: --repeat, create multiple tasks from one prompt, range is 1-40, default is 1

description.seed.message: --seed, initial visual noise of the generated image, range is 0-4294967295, default is randomly generated

description.stop.message: --stop, stop the task at any stage of the generation process, range is 10-100, default is 100 (i.e., fully generated)

description.style.message: --style, switch between different versions or styles of the Midjourney or Niji model, such as raw, cute, expressive, original, scenic, default value depends on the model and mode

description.stylize.message: --stylize, adjust the strength of the default aesthetic style applied in the generation task, range is 0-1000, default is 100

description.tile.message: --tile, generate an image that can be used to create seamless tiling, no default value

description.turbo.message: Override current settings, run a single task in 'turbo mode', no default value

description.weird.message: --weird, explore unconventional aesthetics with an experimental nature, range from 0-3000, default is 0

description.translation.message: Enable automatic translation during generation, non-Chinese content will be automatically translated to English input for Midjourney

description.imageWeight.message: --iw, adjust the weight of the image prompt relative to the text prompt, range from 0-2, default is 1

description.niji.message: --niji, when enabled, the generated images will use the Niji model to create anime-style images

description.uploadReferences.message: Upload images as references for generation, supports up to 5 images. If more than 1 image is uploaded, they will be automatically merged

description.raw.message: --raw, when enabled, the generated images will use the Midjourney model to create original style images

description.prompt.message: Enter a command, if additional parameters are added, they will override the default preset parameters, for example adding '--stylize 200' will force the final command to use '--stylize 200'

model.general.description: Model name used for general image generation

model.niji.description: Model name used for anime-style image generation, do not translate, keep as 'Niji'

name.model.description: Model name, a term used in machine learning for generating images

name.aspect.description: Name of the aspect ratio parameter

name.chaos.description: Name of the chaos parameter, translated as 'Chaos Level'

name.fast.description: Name of the fast mode, used for quick image generation, translated as 'Fast Mode'

name.nijiStyle.description: Name of the nijiStyle parameter, do not translate, keep as 'Niji'

name.imageWeight.description: Name of the image weight parameter

name.no.description: Name of the exclude parameter, used to exclude specific elements, translated as 'Exclude'

name.quality.description: Name of the quality parameter, used to set the quality of the generated image

name.random.description: Name of the random parameter, used to add random style effects

name.relax.description: Name of the relax mode, used to generate images in 'slow speed' mode, translated as 'Slow Mode'

name.repeat.description: Name of the repeat parameter, used to create multiple tasks from a prompt

name.seed.description: Name of the seed parameter, used to set the initial visual noise

name.stop.description: Name of the stop parameter, used to stop the task at any stage

name.style.description: Name of the style parameter, used to switch between different versions or styles of the model

name.stylize.description: Name of the stylize parameter, used to adjust the intensity of the default aesthetic style

name.tile.description: Name of the tile parameter, used to generate images suitable for tiling

name.turbo.description: Name of the turbo mode, used to generate images in 'turbo speed' mode, translated as 'Turbo Mode'

name.weird.description: Name of the weirdness parameter, used to explore uncommon aesthetic styles, translated as 'Weirdness Level'

name.translation.description: Name of the translation parameter, used to enable automatic translation during generation

name.advanced.description: Name of the advanced mode, used to enable advanced mode

name.niji.description: Name of the niji parameter, used to enable the Niji model, do not translate, keep as 'Niji'

name.ignore.description: Name of the ignore parameter, used to ignore certain elements

name.prompt.description: Name of the prompt parameter, used for inputting drawing commands

name.raw.description: Name of the raw parameter, used to enable the Midjourney model
